HEADWORD: Perineurium
<hw>Per`i*neu"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>peri`</grk> about + <grk>ney^ron</grk> a nerve.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The connective tissue sheath which surrounds a
bundle of nerve fibers. See <er>Epineurium</er>, and
<er>Neurilemma</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perinuclear</ent>⟦br⟧
